        <briefdescription>
<para>Defines bitmask flags for clearing render buffers before drawing. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>These flags can be combined using bitwise OR operations to specify which buffers (color, depth, stencil) should be cleared before rendering.</para>
<para>Example usage: ```cpp // Clear both color and depth buffers int clearFlags = std::to_underlying(ClearFlags::Color) | std::to_underlying(ClearFlags::Depth); viewport.setClearFlags(clearFlags); ```</para>
